    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-23T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3084. Your 3949, March 14. <persName>Mitchell</persName>-Bissell application for
                    porcelain guides and cyanide application have been pending since November with
                    constant promises of consideration. Department urges immediate reply as delay is
                    intolerable. Carefully review previous cables and press <persName
                        corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> for an immediate reply on both
                    these matters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
